11 In his notice of appeal the appellant stated the questions of law raised on the appeal as follows:


 "2.1 Whether on the evidence before the Tribunal it was reasonably open for the Tribunal to find: 




 (a) that the sales income of the Appellant for the year of income ended 30 June 1997 was $1,101,758; 
 (b) that the Appellant did not bring into account for taxation purposes cash sales receipts in the amount that equals or exceeds $44,800; 
 (c) that the purchases for the year of income ended 30 June 107 were $872,117; 




 2.2 Whether on the findings of fact made by the Tribunal that $44,800 of the bankings for the year of income ended 30 June 1997 represented funds provided by the Appellant's father it was reasonably open for the Tribunal to conclude that the Appellant has failed to discharge the burden of showing that the assessments were excessive.
